  "texts": [
    "127 Treleaven et al. [156] 2023 Legal Setting \"AI hallucination\" is defined as a confident response that is biased, too specialized, or even entirely incorrect, with the model fabricating a seemingly plausible but factually inaccurate answer.",
    "128 Ariyaratne [157] 2023 Legal Setting \"AI Hallucination\" refers to the term used to describe the phenomena of generative algorithms making up facts. 129 Wu et al.",
    "[158] 2023 Large Language Model \"AI hallucination\" occurs when the replies generated by ChatGPT frequently contain factual errors. 130 Wang et al.",
    "[159] 2023 Large Language Model \"AI hallucination\" occurs when ChatGPT produces responses that, despite sounding plausible, are ultimately incorrect or nonsensical. 131 Amaro et al.",
    "[160] 2023 Large Language Model \"AI hallucination\" occurs when ChatGPT generates outputs that invent facts and concepts, as it lacks objective training to assess the factual correctness of its responses."
  ]
}